  "The cytoskeleton consists of only one type of protein fiber (collagen) that provides rigidity вАФ it has no role in cell movement or intracellular transport": "",
  "The three main components are: (1) microfilaments (actin, ~7 nm diameter) вАФ involved in cell movement, muscle contraction, cytokinesis, and cell shape; (2) microtubules (tubulin, ~25 nm diameter) вАФ form the mitotic spindle, cilia/flagella, and intracellular transport tracks for motor proteins (kinesin and dynein); (3) intermediate filaments (~10 nm, e.g., keratin, vimentin, neurofilaments) вАФ provide mechanical strength and resist tensile forces": "",
  "Cytoskeleton вАФ the cell's internal framework: (1) Microfilaments (actin filaments): thinnest (~7 nm). Composed of G-actin monomers polymerized into F-actin (double helix). Functions: cell shape (cortical actin network beneath membrane), cell movement (lamellipodia, filopodia вАФ amoeboid movement), muscle contraction (actin + myosin sliding filament model), cytokinesis (contractile ring pinches cell in two), microvilli (intestinal epithelium вАФ increase surface area 20√Ч). Dynamic: constant polymerization/depolymerization (treadmilling). Drugs: cytochalasin B (blocks polymerization), phalloidin (stabilizes filaments). (2) Microtubules: largest (~25 nm). Composed of ќ±-tubulin and ќ≤-tubulin heterodimers forming hollow tubes. Functions: mitotic spindle (separates chromosomes during cell division), intracellular transport (motor proteins: kinesin = + end/anterograde; dynein = вИТ end/retrograde), cell shape, cilia (9+2 arrangement вАФ respiratory epithelium, fallopian tubes) and flagella (9+2 вАФ sperm), centrioles (9√Ч3 arrangement). Emanate from centrosome/MTOC. Drugs: colchicine (blocks polymerization вАФ used for gout), taxol/paclitaxel (stabilizes вАФ anticancer drug, prevents mitotic spindle disassembly), vincristine/vinblastine (block polymerization вАФ anticancer). (3) Intermediate filaments: medium (~10 nm). Most stable/least dynamic. Types: keratins (epithelial вАФ hair, nails, skin), vimentin (mesenchymal вАФ connective tissue), neurofilaments (neurons вАФ axon caliber), lamins (nuclear lamina вАФ structural support for nucleus), desmin (muscle). Functions: mechanical strength, resist shearing forces, anchor organelles. Not found in many single-celled eukaryotes.": "",
