  "Endoplasmic reticulum: (1) Largest membrane-bound organelle (>50% of total cell membrane in some cells). Continuous with outer nuclear membrane. (2) Rough ER (RER): ribosomes on cytoplasmic surface. Functions: co-translational translocation (signal peptide вЖТ SRP вЖТ ER translocon вЖТ polypeptide enters ER lumen), protein folding (chaperones: BiP/GRP78, calnexin/calreticulin), N-linked glycosylation (core oligosaccharide GlcвВГManвВЙGlcNAcвВВ transferred to Asn-X-Ser/Thr), disulfide bond formation (PDI вАФ protein disulfide isomerase), quality control (ERAD: ER-associated degradation of misfolded proteins вЖТ retrotranslocated to cytoplasm вЖТ ubiquitinated вЖТ proteasome). (3) Smooth ER (SER): no ribosomes. Functions: phospholipid synthesis (phosphatidylcholine, phosphatidylethanolamine, phosphatidylserine вАФ flippases transfer to inner leaflet), steroid hormone synthesis (abundant SER in adrenal cortex and gonads), detoxification (cytochrome P450 monooxygenases in liver вАФ oxidize drugs, toxins, ethanol; chronic alcohol вЖТ SER proliferation вЖТ increased drug tolerance), calcium storage/release (sarcoplasmic reticulum = specialized SER in muscle: Ca¬≤вБЇ released via ryanodine receptors вЖТ muscle contraction; SERCA pump returns Ca¬≤вБЇ). (4) ER stress and unfolded protein response (UPR): accumulation of unfolded proteins activates three pathways (IRE1, PERK, ATF6) вЖТ increase chaperone production, reduce protein translation, activate ERAD. If overwhelmed вЖТ apoptosis.": "а§Єа§Ѓа•Ба§¶а•На§∞ - а§§а§≤ а§Ѓа•За§В а§Ца§Ља§≤а§Ња§∞а•Ла§≤а§Њ (а§Єа•На§≤а§Ња§≤а§Ња§≤а§Ња§∞а•Ла§≤а§Њ), а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞ (а§Єа•На§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§≤а§Њ), а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞ (а§Єа•На§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§≤а§Њ), а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞ (а§Єа•На§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§≤а§Њ), а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§∞ (а§Єа•На§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§∞а•Ла§≤а§Њ), а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§Њ, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§Њ, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§Њ, а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§Њ, а§ѓа§Њ а§ђа§Ча•Ба§≤а§Њ, а§Фа§∞ а§ђа§Ча•Ба