  "Lysosome вАФ cellular digestive system: (1) Discovery: Christian de Duve (Nobel Prize 1974) вАФ discovered through cell fractionation (differential centrifugation) studying acid phosphatase. Coined 'lysosome' from Greek: lysis (loosening) + soma (body). (2) Structure: single membrane. Interior pH 4.5-5.0 (vs. cytoplasmic pH 7.2) maintained by vacuolar HвБЇ-ATPase proton pumps (V-ATPase). Safety mechanism: if lysosome ruptures, acid hydrolases are inactive at cytoplasmic pH. (3) ~50+ hydrolytic enzymes: proteases (cathepsins), lipases, nucleases, glycosidases, phosphatases, sulfatases. All are acid hydrolases with optimal activity at pH ~5. (4) Pathways: autophagy (damaged organelles/proteins enclosed by autophagosome вЖТ fuses with lysosome вЖТ autolysosome вЖТ digestion; Ohsumi, Nobel 2016), phagocytosis (immune cells: phagosome + lysosome вЖТ phagolysosome), endocytosis (receptor-mediated вАФ e.g., LDL cholesterol uptake: LDL receptor вЖТ clathrin-coated pit вЖТ endosome вЖТ lysosome вЖТ cholesterol released). (5) Lysosomal storage diseases (~50 types, ~1/7,000 births collectively): Tay-Sachs (hexosaminidase A deficiency), Gaucher (glucocerebrosidase вАФ most common, treatable with ERT), Fabry (ќ±-galactosidase A), Pompe (acid maltase/GAA), Niemann-Pick (sphingomyelinase types A/B; NPC1/NPC2 type C), Hurler syndrome (ќ±-L-iduronidase вАФ mucopolysaccharidosis I).": "а§≤а§Ња§За§Уа§≤а§Њ вАФ а§Ѓа•За§∞а•Ла§°а•На§∞а§Єа•НвАМ а§§а§Ва§§а•На§∞: (а•І) а§Жа§И. а§ђа•А. а§Жа§И. а§Жа§И. а§Жа§И. а§Жа§И. а§Жа§И. а§Жа§И. а§µа•А.",
  "Which definition BEST describes the cytoskeleton?": "а§Ха•Ма§® а§Єа•А а§™а§∞а§ња§≠а§Ња§Ја§Њ а§Ха•Л а§Єа•Ва§Ъа§ња§§ а§Ха§∞а§§а•А а§єа•И?",
  "A dynamic network of protein filaments within the cytoplasm that provides structural support, maintains cell shape, enables cell movement, and facilitates intracellular transport вАФ consisting of three main components: microfilaments, microtubules, and intermediate filaments": "",
